   OPTIMIZATION AND ROBOTIC APPLICATIONS, ICHORA},
Series = {International Congress on Human-Computer Interaction Optimization and
   Robotic Applications},
Year = {2025},
Note = {7th International Congress on Human-Computer Interaction, Optimization
   and Robotic Applications-ICHORA, Ankara, TURKIYE, MAY 23-24, 2025},
Organization = {Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc; Ted University},
Abstract = {One of the core challenges in robot arm teleoperation is handling visual
   feedback delays, and uncertainties. Many existing approaches employ
   generative models and autoregressive neural networks to address this
   problem. However, these models are often trained on datasets that lack
   physical effects, such as collisions and gravity. We introduce a dataset
   that contains robot interactions with stacked cubes, explicitly
   incorporating physical effects. We propose two small-scale latent
   diffusion transformer models for robot manipulation conditioned on
   initial frames, the initial gripper position, and the gripper actions.
   Using our custom dataset, we evaluate our model and demonstrate its
   ability to predict frames involving collisions and gravity.},
